South African Stocks Rebound From Earlier Decline, Led Higher by Richemont

-- B y   R o b e r t   B r a n d
-- 
2011-04-26T09:54:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-26/south-african-stocks-snap-three-days-of-advances-as-mining-companies-fall.html
South African stocks gained,
rebounding from an earlier decline, led by Cie. Financiere
Richemont SA after an industry report said Swiss watch exports
rose in March.  The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index rose 76.38, or 0.2
percent, to 32,735.24 as of 11:06 a.m. in Johannesburg, after
declining as much as 0.2 percent earlier.  Swiss watch exports rose 16.5 percent in March from a year
before, the Federation of the Swiss Watch Industry reported.
Richemont, the maker of Cartier and Piaget watches, advanced 47
cents, or 1.1 percent, to 42.23 rand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Robert Brand in  Cape Town  at 
 rbrand9@bloomberg.net   To contact the editors responsible for this story: Gavin Serkin
at   gserkin@bloomberg.net . 